title: H.S. football roundup: Alex Morales lifts Manchester over Lodi
text:
H.S. football roundup: Alex Morales lifts Manchester over Lodi October 18, 2015 Last updated: Sunday, October 18, 2015, 12:50 AM FROM STAFF REPORTS | Print 
Senior quarterback Alex Morales threw five touchdown passes Saturday to lead Manchester to a 48-26 victory over Lodi in NJIC Colonial Division action at Haledon. 
The win was the Falcons’ (3-3) first in a division game since 2009, and leaves them at .500 for the first time this late in the season since 2004. Luis Perez and Nas’Mheir Barrett each caught two touchdown passes. 
QUEEN OF PEACE 42, EMERSON 14 (at North Arlington): Fayeson Carney piled up 224 yards of offense and scored three times as the Golden Griffins picked up an NJIC Patriot Division win at Rip Collins Field. 
Derick Suazo threw for 182 yards and two touchdowns. It’s the first time QP has won consecutive games since November 2013. 
WOOD-RIDGE 32, BOGOTA 0 (at Bogota): Josh Paez carried 25 times for 205 yards and four touchdowns to lift the Blue Devils to a Patriot Division win. He also had a sack, an interception and 10 tackles as Wood-Ridge stretched its winning streak to three games. 
EASTSIDE 24, PASSAIC 7 (at Paterson): Lamar Johnson carried 18 times for 147 yards and a touchdown Friday night to lift the Ghosts to a Big North crossover win at Bauerle Field.
